  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Cases of invasive pulmonary aspergillosis secondary to COPD

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Use of voriconazole or itraconazole or amphotericin B or caspofungin or micafungin
             within 4 weeks prior to enrollment

          -  Known allergy to voriconazole

          -  Severe impairment of live or kidney function

          -  Septic shock

          -  Unwilling to sign informed consent
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
